      <title>Woman opens fire at YouTube HQ, wounding 3 before taking own life</title>
      <description><![CDATA[SAN BRUNO, CALIFORNIA  A woman opened fire at YouTube headquarters in San Bruno on Tuesday afternoon, wounding three people before taking her own life. According to law enforcement sources, the shooting was a domestic dispute, with the shooter targeting someone at the campus, according to the L.A. Times. The shooting took place at around 12:46 p.m. in an outdoor cafe on the grounds. It's still unclear if the attacker worked at YouTube. San Bruno Police Chief Ed Barberini told press on Tuesday that one person, believed to be the shooter, was found dead of a self-inflicted gunshot wound, according to the L.A. Times. Three victims were transported to San Francisco General Hospital with gunshot wounds. A 27-year-old woman is in fair condition, a 32-year-old woman is in serious condition  and a 36-year-old man is in critical condition, hospital officials said, according to SFGate.]]></description>
