      <title>China's first homemade aircraft carrier to go on maiden sea trial</title>
      <description><![CDATA[DALIAN, CHINA  Beijing is prepping to get its first domestically-produced aircraft carrier started on sea trials after its unveiling a year ago.The South China Morning Post reports that China's conventionally powered Type 001A aircraft carrier was made using a special Chinese steel, and can carry up to 48 aircraft  eight more than the Liaoning.The ship is set to embark on its maiden sea trial in the northeastern Bohai Sea, just before the PLA Navy's 60th anniversary celebrations on April 23.Basic functions to be tested include power, damage control, radar, and communications systems. The ship may just circle the bay for the trial, but a longer two- to three-day voyage is possible if no issues arise.Unlike the Liaoning aircraft carrier, which is designed to operate independently, the Type 001A is meant to sail with several other vessels as part of a battle group.Getting the ship combat ready will likely take some time, but if all goes as planned, the as yet unnamed carrier might be joining the navy as early as 2019.]]></description>
