      <title>Aussie teen who swallowed slug on a dare now disabled for life</title>
      <description><![CDATA[SYDNEY  A rugby-playing Aussie teen is now confined to a wheelchair for the rest of his life after eating something he really shouldn't have.The Queensland Times reports that back in 2010, Sam Ballard had picked up a garden slug during a drinking session, and turned to his buddies to ask, 'Should I eat it?'When one mate dared him to, the then 19-year-old popped the poor slug into his mouth and swallowed  not knowing it had parasites that would later burst inside his body.Within days, he developed severe leg pain and had to be taken to a doctor, who figured out he had a bad case of rat lungworms and a brain infection.The parasite is typically found in rodents, but can get into slugs or snails via infected rat doo doo.Ballard contracted eosinophilic meningoencephalitis, a type of meningitis. But instead of recovering like most people, he went into a coma for 420 days and came out of it paralyzed from the neck down.At 28, he requires round-the-clock care, since he can't regulate his body temperature, is prone to seizures, and has to be tube fed.It's pretty tragic, and shows just how much damage a split-second of silliness can actually cause. So next time you decide to eat a slug, please don't.]]></description>
