      <description><![CDATA[AMAZON LAND  Amazon announced a new service this week that can get your ultra unimportant purchases to you as quickly as possible  all you have to do  let couriers into your car. Instead of using smart locks and a cloud-connected camera to gain entry, Amazon uses embedded technology already in vehicles. The online retail juggernaut is partnering with GM and Volvo at first and offering the service in 37 cities across 'Murica. Packages that are too big or heavy, need a signature or are worth over $1,300 aren't eligible for in-car delivery.  Sounds like an Amazon amazing plan. What could possibly go awry?]]></description>
